>Before learning elemetary math, you should learn to read. He proposed to
>try every GENERATED key, not all possible ones. Even if every american
>househould uses clipper one day this would be just around 150.000.000 keys.

This notion is based on complete and utter ignorance of clipper.
Possessing even the actual known escrow key for a chip is useless
unless the intercepted LEAF can be decrypted with it and includes the
actual session key. Forged LEAFs possess neither of these properties.

